  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT247-kilavi">1.kaṭinakart tēlivu vilaṅkiṉmai aṟiyat tōḻi kūṟiyatu. 2. varaivuṭaṉpaṭṭa
          tōḻi talaimakaṭkuk kūṟiyatūumām. </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">1. Spoken by the confidante in order to know of the absence
          of obstacles to clarity (placidity?) in the marriage house. 2. Spoken by HER to the
          confidante who had consented to marriage. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT247">
          <l>eḻiṉmika vuṭaiya tīṅkaṇip paṭūun</l>
          <l>tiṟavōr ceyviṉai yaṟava tākuṅ</l>
          <l>kiḷaiyuṭai māntarkkup puṇaiyumā rivveṉa</l>
          <l>vāṅkaṟin ticiṉē tōḻi vēṅkai</l>
          <l>vīyā meṉciṉai vīyuka yāṉai</l>
          <l>yārtuyi liyampu nāṭaṉ</l>
          <l>mārpurit tākiya maṟuvi ṉaṭpē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>Possessing much grace it grows close <note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">aṇip paṭuum</term>
            : how to understand the morphology and the syntax? <term xml:lang="ta">aṇi</term>presumably
            should be understood as DEDR 120, verbal root "to join with" or adv. "near". T.V.G.
            reads the first line as two sentences, one about the friendship possessing beauty, the
            other about marriage: "[marriage] is coming near for us".</note> here,</l>
          <l>the faultless intimacy that is worthy of the chest</l>
          <l>of the man from the land,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">where the elephant bull rumbles in [his] deep sleep,</l>
          <l rend="indent4">so that the blossoms fall from soft twigs</l>
          <l rend="indent5">without the Vēṅkai being destroyed. <note place="foot">Is the inset to
            be understood symbolically: HE goes away from HER to do his work, but that does not
            shatter the friendship, just as the trumpeting of the elephant costs the <term xml:lang="ta">Vēṅkai</term>some of its flowers, but does not bring it to ruin?</note>
          </l>
          <l rend="indent">“The work to be done is duty to an able man.</l>
          <l>This [is] also a support for people who have relatives” <note place="foot">How to
            understand the syntax? And what is the relation to the rest of the poem? SHE is content
            that HE has gone abroad because this is his duty?</note>
          </l>
          <l rend="indent2">– thus you may know, friend.</l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="4b">
            <l>thus I have understood, friend.</l>
          </lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
